<qhelp>

<overview>
  <p>
    SQL cursor declarations are not executable statements and, as such,
    do not belong in the procedure division. 
  </p>
</overview>

<recommendation>
  <p>
    Define cursor declarations in the data division instead of the procedure division.
  </p>
</recommendation>

<references>
  <li>
    IBM Knowledge Center:
    <a href="http://www.ibm.com/support/knowledgecenter/SSEPEK_10.0.0/sqlref/src/tpc/db2z_sql_declarecursor.html">DECLARE CURSOR</a>.
  </li>
</references>

</qhelp>
